By default, ARCs land in an &#39;arc&#39; subdirectory of your job directory, 
which is itself usually in the &#39;jobs&#39; directory of your installation.

If you are not very familiar with Tomcat, why choose to run with the 
&#39;.war&#39; file inside Tomcat? It&#39;s easier to use the default bundled Jetty 
server -- just launch Heritrix from the command-line and visit the web 
UI. The &#39;jobs&#39; directory is then just a subdirectory of your Heritrix 
install directory.

- Gordon @ IA

